div.div: Fig. 3.The heatmaps produced by this pipeline for segment 4. The y-axis encodes the sample strains, with the pandemic strains labels highlighted in red. The x-axis encodes the length of the reference segment 4 genome, divided into 100 base-long regions. The cells encode the total number of mutations in each sample per every 100 nucleotides, with a higher number of mutations encoded by a darker colour. The cells are annotated with the number of mutations too.
